{
  "stem": "10272.7",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they don't take-- we didn't have all this insurance coverage.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We didn't have the money.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Somehow, we-- my daughter-- our daughter helped us to get all these doctors.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she got the best medication and treatment.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, my first daughter in America is Rachel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She's married to Gabriel Borenstein.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the other daughter's name is Nahama.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She's married to an Israeli boy by the name of Cohen, [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Jakob ?] Cohen.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Today she is Nahama Cohen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they are both very happy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they're trying to make it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nahama's grandchildren are, the, the first was [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Maya, ?] a girl; and then second one is [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Liat, ?] also a girl.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the third one is a boy by the name of Oren.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So she has three children.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She is very happy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Especially this boy-- she is so happy that she has this boy with blue eyes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that she couldn't-- she couldn't over it when she had him, when she saw what a nice boy she has.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So they are happy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he's doing well, now, in Israel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They are both doing well.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they are happy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, in Israel, I was-- I belonged to an organization that arranged once a year-- we met-- like, the-- those who are from, from a certain area, they met together, right?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and-- like when you go to a school, and you met your friends from school.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How do you call--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A reunion.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had this reunion every year.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We get together.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we, we, we, we-- they-- we give money to, to have this in, in such a place like a-- like a Jewish synagogue, put on the wall names of those who, who, who died from, from our town.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we exchange stories.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And over there, I met from our town-- once we had this reunion, we went to Yad Vashem.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In Jerusalem, there is a museum, Holocaust museum, by the name of Yad Vashem.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there, I met many, many people from not from our town-- not only from our town, from the surrounding villages, too.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was a doctor in our town by the name of Davidovitch.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He treated me when I was sick.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he know-- he knew my family and my parents.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was also-- he was also deported to this Kamenets-Podolskiy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there was another lady, which I didn't know her there or then.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She told me she was from Bustino.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't never saw her.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But she says, you were too young boy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You don't remember me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she-- and the-- And these two people, Davidovitch and this lady, is telling me two contradicting stories.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because Davidovitch is telling me the whole story how it-- how it started.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And also, [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Bela's ?] father-- Zelinger was his name.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I met him, also.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he told me a different story also.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Zelinger was the most reliable and credible person because he was our neighbor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he went-- they took him, with my father, on the same train.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The other two which told me the stories, they were not taken by the-- at the same train.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There were different transports, deportations on different dates.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Davidovitch said that he heard from somebody that my parents were in this place called [NON-ENGLISH] in a-- in a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And from [NON-ENGLISH], they took them on march over to Kamenets-Podolskiy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then, no-- he didn't ever hear from them any more.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This woman, also this was hearsays only.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She told me that she heard from somebody else that my father-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] allegedly, he committed suicide.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "She heard this.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So that's all what she-- she did no other information, no details, no whatever happened.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That's all what she heard about my father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "About my mother, she knows nothing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And my brothers, she knows nothing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "This Zelinger, he told me what happened.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "He told me, first, how this deportation happened.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "In Bustino, he says, they had the list of people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They went from house to-- where, where the-- where the list says, the dates.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And they told them to pack up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "In one hour, they have to be at the train.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "They gave them a certain time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "My father said, no way.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "He, he grabbed something there in his hand.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "I don't know what he grabbed, a heavy thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And he came to this officer and said, listen, you're not going to tell me to go from here.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Or you kill me here-- or I kill you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "This officer, with, with, with this-- with this-- not a handgun, this-- he had the such a big gun, a shotgun.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "He hit my father over his head.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "My father ran out.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
